<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Ecolab (ECL)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Ecolab Inc. — using actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })} · Data: FY2025</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">{roundedIV !== null ? `$${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of {currentPrice !== null ? `$${currentPrice.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'} {marginOfSafety !== null ? `(${marginOfSafety}%)` : ''}</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{revenue[0] !== null ? `$${(revenue[0] / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FY2025 Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{fcfArr[0] !== null ? `$${(fcfArr[0] / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{eps[0] !== null ? `$${eps[0].toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{op_income[0] !== null && revenue[0] !== null ? `${(op_income[0] / revenue[0] * 100).toFixed(1)}%` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{netCash !== null ? `$${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Ecolab generated <strong>{fcfBase !== null ? `$${fcfBase.toLocaleString()} million` : 'N/A'}</strong> in free cash flow in FY2025. This is operating cash flow minus capital expenditures. This represents the real cash the business produces after investing to maintain and grow its operations in the water, hygiene, and infection prevention sectors.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. Ecolab is a steady, defensive compounder with significant pricing power and recurring revenue models ("razor-and-blades"). This growth rate reflects steady organic growth and operational efficiencies.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(0)}% forever</strong> — roughly GDP growth plus pricing power. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate). This captures all value from Year 6 to infinity.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(finalDiscountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This aligns with the cost of equity for a mature, lower-risk industrial company with a beta of ~{safeBeta !== null ? safeBeta.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}. It reflects a solid equity risk premium over the 10Y Treasury (4.18%).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash ({netCash !== null ? `$${netCash.toLocaleString()}M` : 'N/A'}) = Equity Value. We divide by diluted shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding !== null ? `${sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}M` : 'N/A'}) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Ecolab benefits from a razor-and-blades model where its installed base of dispensers generates predictable, recurring chemical sales. The company has demonstrated consistent pricing power and steady volume growth. We assume an 8% FCF growth rate, which aligns with long-term historical averages and expected margin expansion.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(finalDiscountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. Equity risk premium: ~5.5%. Beta: {safeBeta !== null ? safeBeta.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}. CAPM suggests a cost of equity around {calculatedWacc !== null ? `${(calculatedWacc * 100).toFixed(1)}%` : 'N/A'}. We use 9% as a reasonable hurdle rate for a high-quality, wide-moat, and defensive business.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. Ecolab provides essential hygiene, water, and infection prevention solutions that are deeply embedded in customer operations, making it highly resilient. We assume it tracks long-term economic expansion indefinitely.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

